{ Here I want to talk briefly about the move order of the Scotch gambit. It is also possible to get the same positions covered in the course through another very popular move order. If you already play 3.Bc4 instead of 3.d4, you can add either of the mainlines to your repertoire without any issues. } 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4f7][%csl Gc4,Rf7]With this move it is also possible to reach the Scotch gambit. } 3... Nf6 ( 3... Bc5 4. c3 { A very forcing move! We are ready to play d4 and Black has nothing better than to play ...Nf6. } 4... Nf6 $146 5. d4 { Striking in the center. } 5... exd4 6. cxd4 Bb4+ 7. Nbd2 $146 { We have now transposed to the 4...Bc5 mainline reached in chapters 2 to 4 in the course. } ) 4. d4 $1 { Here Black has to take. } 4... exd4 { Now we continue with } 5. e5 { [%cal Ge5f6][%csl Ge5,Gf6]And we have transposed to 4...Nf6 in the Scotch gambit. } * 

[Event "The Fast and Furious Scotch Gambit"]
[Site "Introduction to Key Themes"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
