sition remains complex, but at least we managed to exchange Queens and our Knight will land on f5 and guard the g7-pawn. Hopefully, this position will be tested more in practice.” [--] While the position is by no means better for us, we will be better prepared, we will look further in the position and have a much better idea of what to do than our opponent. } 19. Qxf5 { We are forced to trade Queens. } 19... Nxf5 20. Re4 $36 { [%cal Gg5g6][%csl Rh7]I believe that White has a lot of play here. Even in the endgame being down a pawn, the initiative continues. The engine still gives the = evaluation, which means that we have full compensation and more for the pawn. Black can easily go wrong. I believe that from here onwards, GM Werle's followers are already out of book. } 20... Ng3 { [%cal Gh7e4,Gg5g6,Gf7g6,Gf8f3][%csl Re4]A discovery on the Rook while attacking the h5-pawn. } 21. Rg4 { [%cal Gg1g7,Gg5h6][%csl Rg7,Rg3]We are now ready to take on h6 and open lines towards the Black King. A tense fight continues in which Black will have to defend well. } * 

