 Bxc6 $1 { The traditional Scotch gambit move! White gives up the light-squared Bishop in order to double Black's pawns and to speed up our own development. The Black Knight on c6 was also targeting the e5-pawn, so it we were obligated to eliminate it. } 8... bxc6 { [%csl Rc6,Rc7,Gd4,Rd5,Ge1,Ge5]Black's c-pawns are now doubled. However, do not be fooled! If these pawns can get mobile and Black stabilizes their position, these pawns can wreak havoc in White's position. In the Scotch gambit, the aim is very clear: White either fights against the doubled c-pawns or tries to give mate. } 9. O-O { In Scotch gambit style, White finishes development and prepares for the attack! Now } 9... Be7 { [%cal Ge8g8,Gc6c5][%csl Rd4]Black humbly develops their Bishop and leaves room for the c6-pawn to advance. This is the second most popular move in the position and a very reasonable one! } ( 9... Bc5 { is clearly the mainline and the most-played move by Black. However, we should also be aware of } ) ( 9... c5 { and } ) ( 9... Be7 { . } ) ( 9... c5 { is not so great, but } ) ( 9... Be7 { is a very solid move which, however, requires great precision from Black. } ) 10. f3 { [%cal Gf3e4][%csl Gd4,Re4,Gf3]A thematic Scotch gambit idea. We need to get our f-pawn going and use it as a battering ram against the Black King. } 10... Nc5 { Black keeps the Knight flexible on c5. } 11. f4 { [%cal Gf4f5][%csl Ge5,Gf4]The White pawn mass gets going! } 11... O-O { Black cooly castles and finishes their development. } 12. f5 $1 { [%csl Ge5,Gf5,Rg8]The pawns are getting closer and closer! We have two bones in the throat of Black's position: e5 and f5. Black is feeling the pressure as we have these two great assets in the position! We are playing real Barbaric chess here, we just want to crash through and bulldoze Black's position. } 12... Ne4 13. Nb3 $5 { [%cal Gc6c5,Gd1d5][%csl Gb3,Ge5,Gf5]A rare move, which will come as a surprise for our opponent! This is the third most popular move and it is no worse than the main move } ( 13. Nc3 $146 { . I may even argue that it is stronger! [--] With } ) ( 13. Nb3 $146 { we anticipate Black's ...c5 and already move the Knight out of the way and are ready to proceed with our development! } ) 13... Re8 { [%cal Ge7f8,Ge8e5][%csl Re5]The expected move here and played by GM Le Quang Liem against Magnus Carlsen. Black is ready to go after the e5-pawn. } 14. N1d2 { [%cal Gd2e4,Gf1f5][%csl Gd2,Re4,Ge5,Gf5]Here we do not want to get doubled pawns with } ( 14. Nc3 $146 { as Black will simply take } 14... Nxc3 $146 15. bxc3 { and play } 15... Bf8 { . In that scenario the doubled pawns do not benefit us at all. Instead, we want to preserve our pawn structure while eliminating the powerful e4-Knight. } ) 14... Bf8 { [%cal Ge8e5][%csl Re5]Black opens the Rook and puts pressure on the e5-pawn. This was seen in the game of Magnus. } 15. Nxe4 { [%csl Ge4]Getting rid of the stupid e4-Knight - it was not welcome anymore! } 15... dxe4 16. Qd4 $5 { [%cal Gd4e5,Gd4e4,Gb3c5,Gd4c5][%csl Gd4,Re4,Ge5]A multi-functional move! We defend the e5-pawn and attack the e4-pawn. Black is now in the hot seat. } 16... Bc8 $1 { [%cal Gd8d4,Gc8a6,Ga6f1]This was played in the game GM Vocaturo - GM Gledura. It's a very hard move to find, but it's the strongest move! Black now wants to trade Queens as our Queen is holding together our pawn center. } 17. Be3 $14 { [%cal Ge8e5][%csl Re5][%cal Ga1e1][%csl Ge3,Gd4,Gb3][%cal Gb3c5,Ge3a7,Ga2a4][%csl Ga4,Ra7,Rc7,Rc6,Re4]We should avoid With } ( 17. Qxe4 $2 Qd5 { when White's pawn center falls apart. The White Queen has been caught, and in the endgame Black will regain the pawn and be able to use the Bishop pair to exert pressure! } ) ( 17. Be3 { White finishes development and adds support to the center. Black's e4-pawn is still hanging. This is a very hard position to play as Black, as they have a weak e4-pawn and doubled pawns on c6 and c7. However, our pawn on e5 can also become weak. A complex battle lies ahead. [--] If Black plays } 17... a5 { , we can consider either } 18. a4 { if you want a simpler game, or } ( 18. Rae1 { if you want a fully-fledged fight! } ) ) * 

