1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 { [%cal Gc4g8,Ge1g1][%csl Rf7]} 4... Bc5 5. c3 { [%csl Gc3,Rd4]} 5... Nf6 { [%cal Gf6e4][%csl Re4]} 6. cxd4 Bb4+ { [%cal Gb4e1,Gf6e4][%csl Ge1,Re4]} 7. Nbd2 $5 { The gambit that I recommend in the course! Perhaps it is not the first time you see this move, but there will be a huge twist and new idea later in the mainline! } 7... Nxe4 { [%cal Ge4d2,Gb4e1][%csl Rd2]The most popular move and the most correct move. Black was offered a pawn, takes an important central pawn and waits for White to prove the compensation! } 8. d5 $1 { [%csl Rc6]Again establishing a bone in the throat of Black's position and kicking away the Knight. } 8... Ne7 { Black retreats the Knight without making any exchanges. } 9. O-O { [%cal Gd2e4][%csl Re4]} 9... Nxd2 { Black seeks to trade pieces to relieve some pressure. } 10. Nxd2 $1 { [%cal Gb4e1][%csl Gc1]We take back with the Knight in order not to allow Black to trade off the Bishop pair! } 10... O-O 11. a3 { [%cal Ga3b4][%csl Rb4]Going after the Bishop. We are like the hunter in the forest hunting our prey at every turn. } 11... Ba5 { Black is now ready to continue with ...d6 and finish the development while being up a pawn. White has to do something! } 12. d6 $1 { [%csl Rc8,Rd6,Re7]A very powerful move, keeping the Bishop buried on c8. } 12... cxd6 13. Ne4 $14 { [%cal Ge4d6,Gc4f7,Gd1d6][%csl Rc8,Rd6,Ge4,Rf7]White greatly improves the Knight and is ready to take back on d6! } 13... d5 $1 { [%cal Gd5e4,Gd5c4][%csl Gc8,Rd5]Black plays very smartly! They are immediately trying to open the c8-Bishop, even at the cost of giving back both pawns. } 14. Bxd5 Nxd5 15. Qxd5 { [%cal Gc1g5,Gd5a5][%csl Ra5]} 15... d6 { [%cal Gc8h3][%csl Gc8,Rd6]Finally the Bishop is free! } 16. Bg5 { [%cal Gg5d8][%csl Rd8]Our own Bishop comes out with deadly effect. Black has to remain on their toes! } 16... Qc7 $4 { Black seemingly moves the Queen away from danger. } 17. Bf6 $3 { [%cal Gd5g5][%csl Gf6,Rg8]A deadly blow aimed at the Black King! Black's position immediately collapses after this. } 17... gxf6 18. Nxf6+ { [%cal Gf6g8][%csl Rg8]} 18... Kh8 19. Qh5 { [%cal Gh5h7,Gh5a5,Gc7a5,Gc7c2][%csl Ra5,Rc7,Gf6,Rh7]Black can only defend against mate by playing } 19... Qc2 { , but this drops the Bishop on a5 to } 20. Qxa5 { . } * 

