t move, destroying Black's pawn structure. } 18... gxf6 19. Bxa5 $14 { [%cal Ga5c3,Gc3f6,Ga1d1,Gf1e1,Ge1e3,Ge3g3][%csl Rd6,Rf6,Rf7,Rg8]Black is up a pawn but has many pawn weaknesses and an exposed King. This is a very safe, risk-free position to play as White. } * 

