nd supporters with the power of our Bishop pair. [--] White is down a pawn for the moment, but if there is anything that you will learn from this course, is that we don't mind sacrificing a pawn for active play and the initiative. [--] Black has less space for the pieces and not much room to maneuver. We have very simple play while Black has to proceed carefully. } 14. b4 $5 { [%cal Gc5b4,Ga3b4,Ga1a7,Gc1b2,Gb2g7][%csl Ra7,Rg7,Rg8]The most forcing move! White is moving fast and with urgency, which is how we roll in the Scotch Gambit! We do not care about undoubling Black's c-pawns. We want to activate our a1-Rook and put our Bishop on the monster diagonal. [--] The Shankland followers are already stumped. IM Nguyen covers this move in his course, he has done his research! Note that this position has been reached in only 2 games! } 14... cxb4 { Played in both games. Black undoubles their pawns. } 15. axb4 { [%cal Ga1a7,Ga1a3,Ga3g3,Gg3g8,Gc1b2,Gb2g7][%csl Ra7,Rg7,Rg8]} 15... Nf5 { [%cal Gf5d6][%csl Gd6]Played in both games and the idea that Mr. Shankland suggested. } 16. Qc2 $1 { [%cal Gc2h7,Gc2c7,Gf5d4,Gc2c3][%csl Rc7]A brilliant prophylactic move and novelty, aimed against ...Nd6! We keep an eye on c7 and look towards h7 at the same time. } 16... Nd6 { [%cal Gd6c4,Gc2h7][%csl Rc4,Rh7]The Knight is the best blockader, so Black blockades our d-pawn. } 17. Bd3 { [%cal Gc2h7][%csl Gc2,Gd3,Gd5,Rh7]The Queen and Bishop work well together, pointing at the King! } 17... h6 { [%cal Gc2h7]} 18. Ra3 $40 { [%cal Ga3g3,Gc1h6,Gd3h7,Gc1b2][%csl Gc2,Gd3,Rg8]With 16.Qc2 we stepped into unknown waters that no one has dared to venture into yet. The move } ( 18. Ra3 { is a very high-class move. } ) ( 18. Bb2 { was also possible to continue the fire; you can choose either. } ) ( 18. Bb2 { has ideas of Rfc1 and also Ra3 later. Meanwhile, with } ) ( 18. Ra3 { we introduce the idea of bringing the Rook to the Kingside. We can clear the way for the Rook with Bh7+ in some cases and then bring the Rook to g3. Our Bishop on c1 can still decide between b2 and f4. The position is full of fight. } ) * 

