[Result "*"]

1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 exd4 4. Bc4 Nf6 { [%cal Gf6e4][%csl Re4]The traditional Scotch gambit! This gambit goes all the way back in time. For some reason unknown to me, it went out of fashion for a very long time, but I think it is time to bring it back! [--] The traditional Scotch gambit is just what we need: it's very dynamic, aggressive, cuts to the point, and goes for the full point. The engine has found many ways for Black to 'equalize', but I have found many ways to pose problems to Black, for instance with a very creative novelty that we will see in one of the mainlines. [--] Let us bring back the Romantic era of chess. No more boring slow Italians or Ruy Lopez, but let us play fighting chess! You have a very aggressive, swashbuckler's repertoire in front of you that is also backed by the strongest engines! Be ready for a journey and get ready to unlock your inner dragon, bringing out the fire on the board! } 5. e5 { [%csl Ge5,Rf6]Posing a very crucial question to Black. Now } 5... Ng4 { [%cal Gg4e5,Gc6e5][%csl Re5,Gf3]Black goes directly for a counter-attack, fighting hard to get rid of our strong e5-pawn! } ( 5... d5 { has always been the most popular move, while } ) ( 5... Ne4 $146 { has risen greatly in popularity in recent years and is a very solid try to equalize. I believe that it is even stronger than the traditional } ) ( 5... d5 { In this chapter we shall disarm } ) ( 5... Ne4 $146 { and } ) ( 5... Ng4 $146 { , and then } ) ( 5... d5 { will be tackled in the following chapters! } ) 6. O-O { We know that the Scotch gambit relies on solid chess principles of development, the activity of pieces and keeping up the initiative! } 6... Be7 { Black is now ready to grab the pawn! } 7. Re1 { [%cal Ge1e5,Gh2h3][%csl Ge5,Rg4]Defending the pawn. Now we are ready to kick the Black Knight back. } 7... d6 { [%cal Gd6e5][%csl Rd6]Black continues the fight for the e5-pawn. } 8. exd6 { [%cal Ge1e8][%csl Gd6,Re7]Opening the Rook towards Black's King. } 8... cxd6 9. Bg5 { [%cal Gg5d8,Ge1e8,Gf3d4][%csl Rd4,Re7,Re8]We are in no rush to take back the pawn! The Bishop comes into the game with great effect. Black is feeling the pressure on e7. } 9... O-O { Black finishes development, but now White will regain the pawn with interest. } 10. Bxe7 Nxe7 11. Qxd4 $14 { [%cal Gb1c3][%csl Gc4,Gd4,Rd6]White has a healthy structure and active pieces while Black has a weak d6-pawn. } * 

