e these two great assets in the position! We are playing real Barbaric chess here, we just want to crash through and bulldoze Black's position. } 12... Bg5 $6 { [%cal Gc1g5][%csl Ge5,Gf5,Rg5]Black feels the pressure and tries to trade some pieces. However, this is a mistake, as Black gives up their powerful dark-squared Bishop! } 13. Nc3 { [%cal Gc3e4][%csl Gc3,Gd4,Re4]White continues their development and gets more forces into the battle. The c3-Knight controls the crucial e4-square. } 13... Re8 { [%cal Ge8e5][%csl Re5]The 2-pawn team of e5-f5 is too powerful! Black puts some pressure on the e5-pawn. } 14. Bxg5 { White finishes development by trading the c1-Bishop for Black's powerful dark- squared Bishop. } 14... Qxg5 15. Qe2 $14 { [%cal Ga1e1][%csl Gc3,Gd4,Ge5,Gf1,Gf5]The White Queen defends the e5-pawn and the remaining Rook on a1 is ready to come into the game. The e5-f5 pawns make Black feel very uncomfortable and limit their space. After developing our pieces we will break through on the Kingside. We are ready to continue with Rae1. } * 

