{ How should White proceed in this complex position? Do you remember the idea? If not, try to figure it out! } 1. Ba2 { [%cal Gd1b3,Gd5b6,Gg2g4][%csl Rb6,Rd5]A very important prophylactic move, avoiding ...Nb6. Now we have a huge threat of Qb3, attacking the b7-pawn and d5-Knight! [--] There are many ideas in this position. If Qb3 does not work on the next move, we have ideas such as g4 to kick the Bishop then improve our Knight to e4. We have the simple Nf1 to open our bishop after which we can think of Ne3 or Ng3 in the near future. It is a very rich position, always be on high alert and compare different ideas! } 1... Nxd4 2. g4 { [%cal Gd4f3,Gd2f3,Gd1d5,Gg4h5,Ga2d5][%csl Rd5,Rh5]Black loses a piece. } * 

