{ In this position an International Master from Hungary went wrong. Can you find the best move for White? } 1. Bf4 { [%cal Gf4d6,Ga1d1,Gf1f6][%csl Rc3,Rd6,Re8,Gf6]A very important move, and actually the only move to continue the attack. The mentioned IM went wrong with } ( 1. Bh6 { . Instead, it is very important to eliminate Black's dark-squared Bishop. This Bishop on d6 is holding together the entire position and White should realize that it needs to be exchanged. We are down a piece and the position is very messy, but getting rid of this Bishop is a very important concept, eliminating a defender. } ) * 

